value.0: The Malkavian Primogen of New York, known only as Ebenezer (or occasionally Professor E, on account of his auspicious labcoat), is a stoic and contemplative man appearing roughly thirty to fourty years of age. Many mysteries and rumours surround him, some suggesting he was a former mage embraced during the dark ages around the time of the betrayal of the Tremere clan against the Order of Hermes. Others point to his labcoat and cold, clinical demeanour, suggesting that he may have once been one of the founding fathers of modern neuroscience that stumbled upon something he shouldn't have. His prismatic-hued spectacles only add to the mystisism, holding no clear or apparent purpose.

The Nosferatu Primogen was once one of Germany's most alluring models during the time of the Second World War, appearing on the cover of Nazi magazines as a living example of the perfect Aryan woman. It is rumoured that she was embraced by a Jewish Nosferatu lurking within the sewers of Berlin, and that her transformation had more to do with delivering a blow to Nazi morale than anything concerning Selene herself.
The claws of a Kindred gifted with the powers of the Protean Discipline are vicious melee weapons capable of inflicting terrible aggravated wounds upon even the most hardy of supernaturals.

Alexei Bratovich Strauss is an elder of clan Ventrue and the regional Prince of the Kindred of New York, installed by the Camarilla Elders nearly a century ago. Prince Strauss, together with his childe Marissa Werner and loyal Brujah Sheriff Joshua Erwin, campaigned for complete Camarilla control of the city, successfully pushing the Anarchist movement out of New York in 1926. The Sabbat was later defeated in 1940, a war which brought former Sheriff Erwin his True Death. Strauss later chose the macabre Nosferatu leatherface known only as 'Julius' as his Sheriff, an act which both affronted and appauled the majority of the Camarilla Elders. Despite this political setback, the Prince and his Sheriff drove off the Inquisition of 1991, keeping the casualties of both Kindred and Kine to a minimum. Prince Strauss has since ruled a relatively peaceful kingdom in New York, as neither the Anarchs, Sabbat, or Inquisitors have returned in great numbers. Alexei is considered something of a local legend and hero amongst local Camarilla Kindred, as his peerless grasp of tactics and decisive management abilities have kept New York safe and relatively casualty-free, even in the face of incurring war.

Clan Tremere is one of the youngest vampire clans, having just come into existence during the dark ages. In the little time since then they have made incredible inroads within vampiric society and are arguably the most powerful clan in the modern nights. This is due in no small part to their strict heirarchy, secretive nature, and mastery of Thaumaturgy, all of which elicit suspicion, fear, and respect from other Cainites. The Warlocks stand as a pillar of the Camarilla and are one its main defenders, despite the fact that they exist almost as a subsect. Some even go so far as to consider themselves the evolution of vampirism, citing their extreme versatility of blood magic and lack of a true clan curse. The Final Nights have many things in store for the Tremere, however, and the more powerful they grow the more their enemies gather.

A crude phenomenon adopted by and almost unique to the ferocious warpacks of the Sabbat Kindred, Shovelheads are a kind of brutish shock troop developed for the purpose of overwhelming their enemies with superior numbers of expendable cannon fodder who, due to their vampiric nature, make nonetheless dangerous opponents. Upon their embrace, a shovelhead childe is buried within the earth, forcing them to claw their way out of the dirt and mud all the while being plagued by hallucinations and visions on account of the cursed mysticism of Vampirism. Those who survive the horrific endeavour, and many indeed do, are stripped of their humanity by the time they gain their freedom, the result being a far more ferocious and arguably stronger vampire due to his or her closer connection to their Beast, while also leaving them with practically no wits or self control to speak of. Shovelheads generally have short lifespans, with only a rare few ever achieving anything prominent within their sect, while the so coined True Sabbat, the very leaders of the Sabbat, partake in far more exclusive rites and are rarely ever born from such primitive beginnings.

Ammo Caliber: .44

Introduced in 1990, the Colt Anaconda is a large frame double-action revolver featuring a full length under-barrel ejection-rod lug and six round cylinder, designed and produced by the Colt's Manufacturing Company. Chambered for the powerful .44 Magnum and .45 Colt centerfire ammunition cartridges, the Anaconda marked the Hartford, Connecticut firm's first foray into the popular large-bore Magnum pistol market.

Due to its high quality of manufacture, the Anaconda is is considered to have lethal stopping power. As such, it grants a bonus 1 to 4 damage on critical hits.

A knife is typically a single or double edged bladed weapon lengthed between ten to twenty centimetres long. Commonly seen in the employ of both soldiers and thugs, the knife is also a capable tool of non-malicious purposes, in which case the blade is used in entirely non-eviscerating activities, where disembowlment is an unnecessary tedium.

The leaders of the Sabbat, clan Lasombra are darwinists, predators, elegant and inhuman. Firm believers in the worthy ruling and the unworthy serving, the Lasombra have maintained their traditions even as they have turned the Sabbat to their own purposes.

Ammo Caliber: 9mm

The Glock family of pistols, once started by famous Glock 17 pistol, was developed by Austrian company Glock Gmbh., previously known for quality knives and entrenching tools. The Glock 17 pistol first appeared at the Austrian Army trials, won it and was adopted by Austrai Army and Police in the early 1980s under the designation of P-80. Since then, the Glock 17 and its descentants become very popular military and law enforcement firearms, being exported in more than 50 countries. Currently, Glocks are chambered in all major pistol calibers, namely 9x17mm Short (.380ACP), 9x19mm Luger, .357SIG, .40SW, 10mm auto and .45ACP. Also, Glocks available in full-size service models, semi-compact models, compact models for concealed/backup carry, and in longslide competition models. Training versions, firing non-lethal practice ammo, also available. 

Due to its high quality of manufacture, the Glock 17 is always considered a mastercraft weapon. As such, it grants a +1 bonus on attack rolls.

If you described a Tzimisce as inhuman and sadistic, it would probably commend you for your perspicacity on the inhumanity, and then demonstrate that your mortal definition of sadism was laughably inadequate. The Tzimisce have left the human condition behind gladly, and now focus on transcending the limitations of the vampiric state. At a casual glance or a brief conversation a Tzimisce appears to be one of the more pleasant vampires. Polite, intelligent and inquisitive they seem a stark contrast to the howling Sabbat mobs or even the apparently more humane Brujah or Nosferatu. However on closer inspection it becomes clear that this is simply a mask hiding something alien and monstrous.

The very form of a Tzimisce is little more than a science experiment. Subject to extensive metamorphisis as the result of Vicissitude, the Tzimisce has managed to craft his very flesh into a hardened carapace that protects against all forms of physical damage.
The claws of a Kindred gifted with the powers of the Protean Discipline are vicious melee weapons capable of inflicting terrible aggravated wounds upon even the most hardy of supernaturals.

While the practice of ghouling is common amongst Kindred society, in no clan is the 'curse' aspect of this vampiric transformation more readily apparent than with Clan Tzimisce. These 'Szlachta" are small, deformed little creatures often used as servants and guard dogs. They are usually remnants of failed experiments in fleshcrafting and bonecrafting; "waste not, want not" being a catchphrase of the Fiends.

While the fleshcrafters of clan Tzimisce make liberal use of ghouled Szlachta to do their bidding, there are occasions when these stunted potential of these creatures proves all the more limited. In such cases, more powerful servants are required. It is from this need that spawned the War Ghoul. While Szlachta are hand crafted from a singular host, the War Ghouls are a conglomerate union of any number of unfortunate test subjects. These once human beings are driven to insanity as their consciousnesses become trapped in one agonizing form fused together from the flesh, bone and sinew of several different people. These walking behemoths stand taller than an average person and swing their unwieldly claws with all the force and subtlety of a mack truck.
